          <actionDate>2015-05-15</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Stop Blood Tomatoes Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires each public or private company that produces or sells products in interstate commerce and has gross annual revenues exceeding $1 million to submit to annual audits of its supply chains by an independent auditor to determine if the chains are free of child labor and forced labor.</p> <p>The independent auditor shall determine in each audit either that:</p> <ul> <li>the company's products are produced without the use of child labor or forced labor; or</li> <li>if the auditor cannot be certain that child labor or forced labor was used, that the company's products may have been produced with the use of such labor.</li></ul>]]></text>
